There twice each day shall youths combine With tender maids to laud thy power divine.

While their white feet shall lightly bound In Salian mode and triply beat the ground.

Me woman charms not, no, nor lad,

Nor idle dream of mutual hearts made glad, Nor jar that bodes the deep carouse,

Nor wreath of opening buds to bind my brows.
